  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Ticket Properties allows users to add additional details to tickets. Properties can filter the Ticket Queue and various reports, and act as triggers for Custom Forms, Automated Notifications, and Approvals based on assigned properties.</p><p>By default, all users who create tickets can designate an Assignee, Action, or Resolution to Repair Tickets. Users with the Manager Role or higher can manually override properties to any ticket type.\u00a0</p><h3 id=\"TicketPropertiesandOverrides-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931411672/Ticket+Properties+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931411672\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ticket Properties Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932394588/Ticket+Properties+Create+a+Ticket+Resolution\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932394588\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ticket Properties: Creating New Ticket Resolutions</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525679/Ticket+Properties+Creating+New+Ticket+Actions\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525679\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ticket Properties: Creating New Ticket Actions</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525658/Ticket+Properties+Search+Tickets+by+Assigned+Properties\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525658\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ticket Properties: Search Tickets by Assigned Properties</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"TicketPropertiesandOverrides-AssigningTicketPropertiestoRepairTickets\">Assigning Ticket Properties to Repair Tickets</h2><p>When creating a new Repair Ticket or editing an existing Repair ticket, properties for Assignee, Action, and Resolution can be found along the top row of the ticket.\u00a0</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Ticket%20Properties%20Override%201.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"TicketPropertiesandOverrides-TicketPropertiesOverride\">Ticket Properties Override</h2><p><strong>Note</strong>: Managers or higher can manually override properties to any ticket type.</p><p /><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933541674/Searching+for+Tickets\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933541674\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Look up a ticket</a> by searching on the main page of RepairQ or by searching your Ticket Queue. On the Ticket View page, click the <strong>Properties Button (gear icon)</strong> on the upper right of the page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Ticket%20Properties%20Override%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>A Ticket Properties modal will appear. Assign new ticket properties as needed and click <strong>Save</strong> to submit your changes.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Status</strong> - Change the status of the ticket.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location</strong> - Change the current location of the ticket.</p></li><li><p><strong>Assignee</strong> - Assign a staff member to this ticket.</p></li><li><p><strong>Action</strong> - Make workflows more detailed by adding customizable actions.</p></li><li><p><strong>Resolution</strong> - Add a resolution to the ticket for reporting purposes.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"380\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Ticket%20Properties%20Override%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You can view the updated properties under the Summary section of the ticket. Changes to ticket properties will also show in the ticket\u2019s Change Log.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"287\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Ticket%20Properties%20Override%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329145/Ticket%20Properties%20Override%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
